                    <h1>Integrating a Lottie Animation</h1>
                    <h2 id="folder-breakdown">Folder Breakdown</h2>
                    <p>When you export a project youâ€™ll see the following structure:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><%= timelineFolder %> (Folder)
                            <ul class="alphabetic">
                                <li>fonts (Folder containing all the fonts used in the lottie animation)</li>
                                <li>img (Folder containing all the images used in the lottie animation)</li>
                                <li>index.html (An html file you can double click to quickly preview the Lottie animation in a browser)</li>
                                <li>README.html (The file you are currently reading)</li>
                                <li><%= timelineName %>.js (A js file used by <code>index.html</code>)</li>
                                <li><%= timelineName %>.json (The actual Lottie JSON file)</li>
                            </ul>
                        </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2 id="integrating-a-single-instance">Integrating the Animation</h2>
                    <p>For instructions on how to integrate Lottie animations into your website/app please see Lottie's documentation:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><a href="https://airbnb.io/lottie/#/web">Web</a> </li>
                        <li><a href="https://airbnb.io/lottie/#/android">android</a> </li>
                        <li><a href="https://airbnb.io/lottie/#/ios">iOS</a> </li>
                        <li><a href="https://airbnb.io/lottie/#/react-native">React Native</a> </li>
                        <li><a href="https://airbnb.io/lottie/#/windows">Windows</a> </li>
                    </ul>

                    <h2 id="Notes">Special Notes for Android</h2>
                    <p>When integrating lottie animations (exported from Flow) which contain text layers you must include the fonts in your android studio project. The font files must be included in the <code>src/main/assets/fonts</code> directory.</p>
